he King issued the order at an Easter celebrations rally that was attended by Christian religious leaders at the Engabezweni Royal Residence, according to Quartz. In our culture, once you marry, there is no turning back, King Mswati declared.He also ordered the clergymen present to inform their followers that marriage should be for life, adding that there is no word for divorce in Siswati, the official language of Swaziland.He is reported to have signed a bill that will finance the enforcement of the new law on Wednesday. The signing of the bill according to local papers, have drawn criticism from NGOs and lawyers. Legal experts and government officials in Swaziland have come out to dispute claims that divorce has been outlawed in the country, arguing that the King s decree is unlawful since he has not officially tabled it in parliament for debate.